The problem only happens if two threads are trying to load the same macro at the same time. The log will contain the following error:
{noformat}
2007-08-14 22:39:53,515 resin-tcp-connection-j2ee.extranet.atlassian.com-jira:6802-39 ERROR [velocity] VM error : createLevelSelect. Null AST
{noformat}

This is caused by by [VELOCITY-514|https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/VELOCITY-514] which in turn seems to be caused by [VELOCITY-24|https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/VELOCITY-24].  JIRA currently depends on Velocity 1.4, and these bugs have been fixed in Velocity 1.5.   A restart will resolve the problem.

We should upgrade JIRA to Velocity 1.5 sometime in the near future (and brace ourselves for any new Velocity bugs ;)).

